chnical imaging processes, and the evolution of film and media studies: discorrelated images herald a transformation of subjectivity itself and are essential to our ability to comprehend nonhuman agency.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aDigital cinematography. 0aDigital images. 0aMotion picture audiences. 0aMotion picture industryxTechnological innovations. 0aMotion picturesxProduction and directionxTechnological innovations. 0aVisual perception. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / History & Criticism.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDuke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311069631808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts 2020z9783110704655oZDB-23-DPK08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2020 Englishz978311070478508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781478012412zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478012412423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781478012412/original  a978-3-11-069631-8  Duke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-070478-5  EBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2020 Englishb2020  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2020  aZDB-23-DPKb2020